Mimikatz is essential in every internal penetration test or red team engagement mainly for its capability to extract passwords from memory in clear-text. It is also known that adversaries are using Mimikatz heavily in their operations. 

Although Microsoft introduced a security patch which can be applied to current operating systems and even older ones such as Windows 2008 Server. Mimikatz is effective and has many use cases. 

Lateral movement 
-PTH with dumped SAM hashes
-Cracking domain hashes that are pulled
-Kerberoasting

Domain escalation. 
-Impersonate Kerberos tickets to find privileged account then make yourself a DA
-
It should be noted that Mimikatz can only dump credentials and password hashes if it is executed from the context of a privilege user like local administrator.









Mimikatz core functionality/commands
```
-----------------------------------------------------------------
    Command           Description
    -------           -----------
    kerberos          Attempt to retrieve kerberos creds
    livessp           Attempt to retrieve livessp creds
    mimikatz_command  Run a custom command
    msv               Attempt to retrieve msv creds (hashes)
    ssp               Attempt to retrieve ssp creds
    tspkg             Attempt to retrieve tspkg creds
    wdigest           Attempt to retrieve wdigest creds
```
